Cape Town - Mystery surrounds the cause of a fire that left scores of people homeless in Blikkiesdorp, outside Cape Town. A fire gutted a home in Blikkesdorp late on Wednesday afternoon. It’s not exactly clear how the fire started, but according to eyewitnesses, the owner of the shack was seen walking away minutes after the informal dwelling burnt down. The owner of the informal structure was anxious on the day her home burnt down, a witness who did not want to be named said. To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window. “I heard one of the children scream 'Ouma come out!' (and) I came out and then I saw the fire. But before that, I saw the lady walking out and she looked extremely cross,” she said. This is not the first time a house in Blikkesdorp had been gutted by a fire. According to residents, two weeks ago a shack burned down two children and a woman died as a result. “That lady with the two children burned and she was pregnant. And here we have another fire. It’s getting dangerous for us,” the resident said.  marvin.charles@inl.co.za  Cape Argus